; Regression test for issue #742: ledger stats ignores -p until (BZ#742)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/742
;
; The stats command must respect the period specification (`-p "until DATE"`),
; --end, --begin, and --limit filters.  Prior to the fix, the stats command
; walked the entire journal unconditionally via family_details(), so those
; filters were silently ignored.  With the command now participating in the
; post filter chain, its output reflects the restricted range.

2012-02-28 * Test
    E               30.00 EUR
    F

2012-02-29 * Test
    E               30.00 EUR
    F

2012-03-24 * Test
    A               30.00 EUR
    B

; -p "until DATE" expands to "date < DATE", so "until 2012-03-01" includes
; Feb 28 and Feb 29 only.  The statistics must reflect just those two
; transactions: 2 accounts (E, F) rather than all 4, and 4 postings rather
; than 6.  `--now` pins CURRENT_DATE() so the recency counters are stable.
test stats -p "until 2012-03-01" --now "2012-03-31"
Time period: 12-Feb-28 to 12-Feb-29 (2 days)

  Files these postings came from:
    $FILE

  Unique payees:               1
  Unique accounts:             2

  Number of postings:          4 (2 per day)
  Uncleared postings:          0

  Days since last post:       31
  Posts in last 7 days:        0
  Posts in last 30 days:       0
  Posts seen this month:       0
end test

; --end 2012/03/01 is equivalent to -p "until 2012-03-01" for stats purposes.
test stats --end 2012/03/01 --now "2012-03-31"
Time period: 12-Feb-28 to 12-Feb-29 (2 days)

  Files these postings came from:
    $FILE

  Unique payees:               1
  Unique accounts:             2

  Number of postings:          4 (2 per day)
  Uncleared postings:          0

  Days since last post:       31
  Posts in last 7 days:        0
  Posts in last 30 days:       0
  Posts seen this month:       0
end test

; --begin excludes postings before the date.  "--begin 2012/03/01" excludes
; Feb 28 and Feb 29, leaving just the 2012-03-24 transaction.
test stats --begin 2012/03/01 --now "2012-03-31"
Time period: 12-Mar-24 to 12-Mar-24 (1 days)

  Files these postings came from:
    $FILE

  Unique payees:               1
  Unique accounts:             2

  Number of postings:          2 (2 per day)
  Uncleared postings:          0

  Days since last post:        7
  Posts in last 7 days:        2
  Posts in last 30 days:       2
  Posts seen this month:       2
end test

; Account queries reach stats through the --limit predicate, so filtering
; by account name must also narrow the reported statistics.
test stats ^A --now "2012-03-31"
Time period: 12-Mar-24 to 12-Mar-24 (1 days)

  Files these postings came from:
    $FILE

  Unique payees:               1
  Unique accounts:             1

  Number of postings:          1 (1 per day)
  Uncleared postings:          0

  Days since last post:        7
  Posts in last 7 days:        1
  Posts in last 30 days:       1
  Posts seen this month:       1
end test
